<html>
  <problem>
    
      <p>A block of mass M is sliding down an inclined plane and is accelerating.  Which of the following statements are true?</p>
    
    <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="yes" loncapaid="11">
      <ul>
        <conceptgroup concept="One">
          <optioninput location="random" name="OneA" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The frictional force must be zero
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="OneB" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The frictional force must be less than the component of Mg down the plane
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="OneC" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The frictional force must be greater than the component of Mg down the plane
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="Two">
          <optioninput location="random" name="TwoA" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The acceleration of the block must be less than g
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="TwoB" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The acceleration of the block is dependent upon the angle of the inclined plane
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="Three">
          <optioninput location="random" name="ThreeA" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The normal force of the plane is equal to the weight of the block
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="ThreeB" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The normal force of the plane is less than the weight of the block
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="ThreeC" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

The normal force of the plane is greater than the weight of the block
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="ThreeD" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

The normal force of the plane is equal to the component of Mg perpendicular to the plane
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="Four">
          <optioninput location="random" name="FourA" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The surface must be frictionless because the block is accelerating
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FourB" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                The surface must have some friction because the block is accelerating
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FourC" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

The surface cannot have any friction because the block is accelerating
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FourD" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

The surface may or may not have friction, even though the block is accelerating
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="">
          <optioninput location="random" name="FiveA" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

If the block's mass were doubled, its acceleration would be doubled
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FiveB" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

If the block's mass were doubled, its acceleration would be halved
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FiveC" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

If the block's mass were doubled, its acceleration would not change
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FiveD" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

If the block's mass were halved, its acceleration would not change
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
      </ul>
      <hintgroup showoncorrect="no">
        
          <p>Add hint text here.</p>
        
      </hintgroup>
    </optionresponse>
  </problem>
</html>
